## Coming Up: Cohort Analysis

The cohort query uses CASE WHEN in a different way — to assign each
subscription to a "month bucket" (M0, M1, M2...) based on how long after
signup an invoice was paid. The syntax is the same pattern:

```sql
CASE
    WHEN months_since_signup = 0 THEN 'M0'
    WHEN months_since_signup = 1 THEN 'M1'
    WHEN months_since_signup = 2 THEN 'M2'
    ...
END AS cohort_month
```

Once you can write CASE WHEN in your sleep — which you will after Steps A
through D — the cohort query is just a new business question, not a new concept.

